{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddb380b56-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s371b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"371b"},"text":"§ 371b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Rate of interest on time deposits; payment of time deposits before maturity; waiver of notice requirements for withdrawal of savings deposits","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Board may from time to time, after consulting with the Board of Directors of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation and the Federal Home Loan Bank Board, prescribe rules governing the advertisement of interest on deposits by member banks on time and savings deposits. The provisions of this section shall not apply to any deposit which is payable only at an office of a member bank located outside of the States of the United States and the District of Columbia. During the period commencing on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-15"},"text":"October 15, 1962","children":[],"tail":", and ending on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1968-10-15"},"text":"October 15, 1968","children":[],"tail":", the provisions of this paragraph shall not apply to the rate of interest which may be paid by member banks on time deposits of foreign governments, monetary and financial authorities of foreign governments when acting as such, or international financial institutions of which the United States is a member."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddb380b57-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1913-12-23/ch6/s19/j"},"text":"Dec. 23, 1913, ch. 6, § 19(j)","children":[],"tail":", formerly § 19 (par. 13), as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1933-06-16/ch89/s11/b"},"text":"June 16, 1933, ch. 89, § 11(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/182"},"text":"48 Stat. 182","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-23/ch614"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1935, ch. 614","children":[],"tail":", title III, § 324(c), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/714"},"text":"49 Stat. 714","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/827/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–827, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-15"},"text":"Oct. 15, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/953"},"text":"76 Stat. 953","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/79/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–79, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1965-07-21"},"text":"July 21, 1965","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/79/244"},"text":"79 Stat. 244","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 19(j) and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/597/s2/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–597, § 2(b)","children":[],"tail":", (c), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-09-21"},"text":"Sept. 21, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/824"},"text":"80 Stat. 824","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/505/s2/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–505, § 2(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1968-09-21"},"text":"Sept. 21, 1968","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/82/856"},"text":"82 Stat. 856","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/221/tII/s207/b/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–221, title II, § 207(b)(4)","children":[],"tail":"–(6), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-03-31"},"text":"Mar. 31, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/144"},"text":"94 Stat. 144","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddb380b58-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddb380b59-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"iddb380b5a-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/221"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–221","children":[],"tail":" struck out provisions relating to payment of interest on deposits, prescribing of different limitations by the Board for different classes of deposits, and payment of time deposits before maturity."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1968—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/505"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–505","children":[],"tail":" gave Board power to prescribe rules governing the payment and advertising of interest on deposits."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1966—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/597/s2/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–597, § 2(c)","children":[],"tail":", made authority of Board to prescribe maximum permissible rates of interest that may be paid by member banks on time and savings deposits discretionary rather than mandatory, required prior consultations with the FDIC Board and the FHLB Board, authorized different rate limitations for different classes of deposits, for deposits of different amounts, or according to such other reasonable bases as the Board may deem desirable in the public interest, and struck out provision for rate limitation according to the varying discount rates of member banks in the several Federal Reserve districts."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1965—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/79"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–79","children":[],"tail":" extended until "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1968-10-15"},"text":"Oct. 15, 1968","children":[],"tail":", the period during which the provisions of this paragraph do not apply to the rate of interest payable by member banks on time deposits of foreign governments, monetary and financial authorities of foreign governments when acting as such, or international financial institutions of which the United States is a member."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1962—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/827"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–827","children":[],"tail":" inserted sentence making this paragraph inapplicable, during the period commencing on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-15"},"text":"October 15, 1962","children":[],"tail":", and ending upon the expiration of three years after such date, to the rate of interest which may be paid by member banks on time deposits of foreign governments, monetary and financial authorities of foreign governments when acting as such, or international financial institutions of which the United States is a member."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1935—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1935-08-23"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1935","children":[],"tail":", among other changes, inserted “except upon such conditions and in accordance with such rules and regulations as may be prescribed by the said Board” to second sentence and proviso."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"iddb380b5b-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"iddb380b5c-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1980 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/221/tII/s207/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–221, title II, § 207(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-03-31"},"text":"Mar. 31, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/144"},"text":"94 Stat. 144","children":[],"tail":", provided in part that the amendment made by that section is effective 6 years after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-03-31"},"text":"Mar. 31, 1980","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"iddb380b5d-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective and Termination Dates of 1966 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/597/s7"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–597, § 7","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-09-21"},"text":"Sept. 21, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/825"},"text":"80 Stat. 825","children":[],"tail":", as amended, formerly set out as an Effective and Termination Dates of 1966 Amendment note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s461"},"text":"section 461 of this title","children":[],"tail":" (which provided in part that amendment of this section by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/597/s2/c"},"text":"section 2(c) of Pub. L. 89–597","children":[],"tail":" was effective only to "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-15"},"text":"Dec. 15, 1980","children":[],"tail":", and that on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-15"},"text":"Dec. 15, 1980","children":[],"tail":", this section was amended to read as it would without the amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/597/s2/c"},"text":"section 2(c) of Pub. L. 89–597","children":[],"tail":"), was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/221/tII/s207/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–221, title II, § 207(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-03-31"},"text":"Mar. 31, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/144"},"text":"94 Stat. 144","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"iddb380b5e-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Federal Home Loan Bank Board abolished and functions transferred, see sections 401 to 406 of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/73"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–73","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1437"},"text":"section 1437 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"iddb380b5f-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Time Deposits; Interest Rates, Limitation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/123"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–123","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-10-15"},"text":"Oct. 15, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/448"},"text":"87 Stat. 448","children":[],"tail":", provided that in carrying out the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-09-21"},"text":"September 21, 1966","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/597"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–597","children":[],"tail":") [enacting "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1425b"},"text":"section 1425b of this title","children":[],"tail":", amending sections 355, 371b, 461, and 1828 of this title and section 771 of former Title 31, repealing "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s462a–1"},"text":"section 462a–1 of this title","children":[],"tail":", and enacting provisions set out as notes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s461"},"text":"section 461 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] and other provisions of law, the Secretary of the Treasury, the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System, the Board of Directors of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation, and the Federal Home Loan Bank Board take action to limit rates of interest or dividends paid on time deposits of less than $100,000 by institutions regulated by them, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/221/tII/s207/b/13"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–221, title II, § 207(b)(13)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-03-31"},"text":"Mar. 31, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/144"},"text":"94 Stat. 144","children":[],"tail":", eff. 6 years after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-03-31"},"text":"Mar. 31, 1980","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
